MODIFICATION (per Apache License 2.0 Section 4(b)): a later addition
integrated quantum-computing peptide-folding tools, a spatial/OpenUSD
export layer, and a multi-endpoint ADMET orchestration tool:
  - src/protein_design_mcp/pipelines/quantum_runner.py (new file) --
    QuPepFold CVaR-VQE wrapper (import-guarded, never crashes the
    server if `qupepfold`/Qiskit/Braket aren't installed) plus a
    CLASSICAL quantum-walk-inspired torsion-angle Metropolis simulation
    with NeRF backbone construction. See that file's module docstring
    for exactly what is/isn't a faithful reproduction of the QFold and
    QuPepFold papers (both cited in CITATION.cff) -- in particular, the
    quantum-walk tool does NOT run an actual quantum circuit simulation.
  - src/protein_design_mcp/tools/predict_peptide_quantum_vqe.py,
    predict_structure_quantum_walk.py, predict_admet_profile.py (new
    files) -- thin MCP tool wrappers, same one-tool-per-file convention
    as the existing predict_bioactivity.py/train_qsar_model.py.
  - src/protein_design_mcp/uag_exporter.py (new file) -- converts atom
    coordinate lists (from Boltz-2, the quantum-walk simulation, or
    elsewhere) into OpenUSD .usda files, for NVIDIA Omniverse/NanoVer/
    Unreal/Unity consumption. Uses real `pxr` USD bindings if
    `usd-core` is installed; otherwise falls back to a hand-written,
    schema-valid ASCII .usda writer with no extra dependency.
  - src/protein_design_mcp/exceptions.py (added QuantumBackendError)
  - src/protein_design_mcp/server.py (added predict_peptide_quantum_vqe,
    predict_structure_quantum_walk, and predict_admet_profile Tool
    schemas, dispatch, and handlers)
  - README.md (documented the 3 new tools under "Available Tools",
    added "Optional Tools: QuPepFold" and "Spatial Digital Twin Export
    (OpenUSD)" sections, updated the architecture diagram, updated all
    tool-count references from 21 to 24 total, and added QuPepFold/
    QFold/OpenUSD entries to "References")
  - pyproject.toml (added `quantum` and `usd` optional-dependency
    extras; documentation only, same as the existing `zairachem` extra
    -- qupepfold's exact PyPI availability/version was not
    independently reverified when this extra was added)
  - claude_desktop_config.json (new file, repo root) -- example config
    for running this server across 4 dependency-isolated venvs. See
    that file's own `_comment_*` fields for a correction made relative
    to a naive per-capability-server design: this repo has one server
    module (server.py), not separate boltz_server.py/quantum_server.py
    modules, and ZairaChem has no `mcp-serve` subcommand of its own.
  - CITATION.cff (new file, repo root) -- includes a software citation
    for qfoldit/Virtual-Lab-Simulation (Neil Voss), added once its
    repository was independently confirmed by direct fetch on
    2026-07-11. Not currently wrapped or vendored by this codebase --
    listed for attribution/context only.
predict_admet_profile additionally depends on one or more
ZAIRACHEM_MODEL_<ENDPOINT> environment variables pointing at trained/
pretrained ZairaChem model directories; endpoints with no configured
model are reported as "not_configured", never given a fabricated score.

